<h1 class="nhsuk-heading-xl">Governance &amp; partnership</h1>

<p class="nhsuk-lead-paragraph">
  The {{ site.owner }} leads the programme and retains overall strategic control. Delivery is a
  partnership between the Observatory and an NHS acute trust, with a digital delivery partner
  appointed through tender.
</p>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">How it works</h2>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>Memorandum of Understanding</strong> between the Observatory (via the NHS Confederation) and the NHS trust, setting out purpose, duration, funding and roles.</li>
  <li><strong>Match funding</strong> shared equally, enabling a single institution to issue delivery contracts and run a private beta.</li>
  <li><strong>Programme board</strong> convened by the Observatory, meeting monthly, including the partners, the delivery partner, and patient representatives from the sickle cell community.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">Roles</h2>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>The Observatory</strong> — strategic direction, commercial and programme delivery, tendering, and the technical and legal infrastructure for a new service.</li>
  <li><strong>The NHS partner</strong> — the clinical setting to operate and evaluate the pilot, with support from haematology, emergency services, and IT.</li>
  <li><strong>The delivery partner</strong> — building the production service to modern digital standards.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">Intellectual property</h2>
<p class="nhsuk-body">
  Intellectual property created in the project is intended to be fundamentally public domain, to
  maximise adoption for the benefit of patients and the NHS. Outputs are published under licences
  designed for sharing rather than monetisation.
</p>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">Timeline</h2>
<ol class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--number">
  <li><strong>Jun – Sept 2026</strong> — partnership development and tender.</li>
  <li><strong>Oct 2026 – May 2027</strong> — digital service build.</li>
  <li><strong>Jun 2027 – Sept 2028</strong> — private beta pilot and iteration.</li>
</ol>
